Depends: iproute2, {{ DEPS }}
Recommends: fdisk, dosfstools, parted, skopeo
Description: bootable OCI container image manager for Debian
 Manages the host operating system as an OCI container image, using
 ostree as the on-disk storage and atomic deployment engine. Enables
 transactional OS upgrades and rollbacks driven entirely by standard
 container tooling and a container registry.
 .
 This is a Debian port of the upstream bootc project, compiled from
 source against the ostree and composefs libraries provided by this
 repository. It is the core component of the debian-bootc image stack.
